The prime minister has confirmed that the 2-metre rule would be dropped in favour of a “1-metre-plus” approach, as people from two different households will be able to drink or dine together from 4 July in England. However, those who are more at risk or vulnerable may choose to continue to maintain the 2-metre rule or wear face masks or gloves. We want to hear from people who have experienced any issues with friends or family over different approaches to physical distancing. We are keen to hear from more than one person in the same family/couple/friendship group, if they have differing views. How has the different interpretations of physical distancing rules impacted your relationship? Have you healed the rift? You can get in touch by filling in the form below. Your responses are secure as the form is encrypted and only the Guardian has access to your contributions. One of our journalists will be in contact for publication before we publish, so please do leave contact details. If you’re having trouble using the form, click here. Read terms of service here.